<section id="right">
  <h3>What's New</h3>
  <p>
    A lot of new features have been added to the Krist API starting in 2020.
    Here's a showcase of some of the new things!
  </p>
  
  <div class="whats-new">
    {{#>new date="2021-02-27" hash="af04c1c" new="true"}}
      Transactions now return the name and metaname they were originally sent
      to, via the <code>sent_name</code> and <code>sent_metaname</code> fields.
      Now you no longer have to parse the metadata!
    {{/new}}

    {{#>new date="2021-02-24" hash="aaeb0a7"}}
      {{#>link url="/motd"}}/motd{{/link}} now returns a lot more info about the
      Krist node and its configuration. It also returns this for websockets
      when they first connect, via the <code>hello</code> message.
    {{/new}}

    {{#>new date="2021-02-20" hash="4dd187f"}}
      A new endpoint ({{#>link url="/work/detailed"}}/work/detailed{{/link}}) 
      has been added to provide quick detailed information about when the block
      value will next decrease if a name has been recently purchased.
    {{/new}}

    {{#>new date="2020-12-23" hash="8356043"}}
      Transactions now return their type (e.g. <code>mined</code>, 
      <code>transfer</code>) everywhere in the API.
    {{/new}}

    {{#>new date="2020-10-01" hash="38f0753" authorUsername="dmarcuse" authorName="Dana Marcuse" }}
      Block submission now supports binary nonces, up to 24 bytes long.
    {{/new}}    

    {{#>new date="2020-09-15" hash="../compare/79117d1303099607a20b0cd73be76f11b100a7e5...55e6b749dfdcde5a6ae5232c485719b60cd0bc2a"}}
      The {{#>link url="/docs/#api-LookupGroup"}}Lookup API{{/link}} has been
      added, allowing you to look up events in bulk (e.g. multiple addresses
      at once, transactions for multiple addresses).
    {{/new}}
  </div>

  {{#if commits}}
    <h3>
      Recent Commits 
      {{#>link url="https://github.com/tmpim/Krist/"}}
        <i class="fa fa-github github-icon"></i>
      {{/link}}
    </h3>

    <div class="git-commits">
      {{#each commits}}
        <a href="https://github.com/tmpim/Krist/commit/{{hash}}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">
          <div class="commit">
            <div class="commit-bar"></div>
            <div class="commit-info">
              <span class="commit-subject" title="{{body}}">
                {{#if type}}
                  <span class="commit-type commit-type-{{type}}">{{type}}</span>
                {{/if}}
                {{subject}}
              </span>
              <div class="author">
                {{#if avatar}}<img class="commit-avatar" src="{{avatar}}" />{{/if}}
                <span class="author-name">{{authorName}}</span>
                <span class="sep">&ndash;</span>
                <span class="date">{{authorDateRel}}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
      {{/each}}
    </div>
  {{/if}}
</section>
